definition.value: An erythronate that is the conjugate base of D-erythronic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (S)-2-hydroxy-3-oxo-4-(phosphonooxy)butanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of (R)-2-hydroxy-3-oxo-4-(phosphonooxy)butanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroperoxydocosapentaenoic acid that is (4Z,7Z,11Z,13Z,15E)-docosapentaenoic acid carrying two hydroperoxy substituents at positions 10 and 17.
A hydroperoxydocosapentaenoic acid that is (7Z,11Z,13Z,15E,19Z)-docosapentaenoic acid carrying two hydroperoxy substituents at positions 10 and 17.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of a 4-hydroxycarboxylic acid.
A leukotriene consisting of 6-trans-leukotriene B4 having a 12-keto group in place of the 12-hydroxy group.
A 3-aminoalanine that has  R configuration.
The zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the beta-amino group of 3-amino-D-alanine. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A steroid sulfate that is 17alpha-ethynylestradiol in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a sulfo group.
A glucan derivative that is (1->4)-alpha-D-glucan in which the 6-position of the repeating unit has been phosphorylated.
An isocyanate comprising a cyclohexane core with a single isocyanato substituent.
An N-acyl-L-phenylalanine resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of arachidonic acid with the amino group of L-phenylalanine.

A biflavonoid that is 3,4,5-trihydroxybenzocyclohepten-6-one which is substituted at positions 1 and 8 by (2R,3R)-3,5,7-trihydroxy-3,4-dihydro-2H-chromen-2-yl groups. It is the main red pigment in black tea.
An L-serine derivative resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with the amino group of L-serine.
An L-glutamine derivative resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with the amino group of L-glutamine.
An L-leucine derivative resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with the amino group of L-leucine.
A fatty acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-hexadecenoic acid with the amino group of glycine.
Organonitrogen compounds that have the general structure R(1)(R(2))C=N(O)OH (R(1),R(2) = H, organyl). They are tautomers of C-nitro compounds.
A fatty acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of octadecanoic acid with the amino group of glycine.
An anionic phospholipid that is the conjugate base of 2,6-O-bis(alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-1-phosphatidyl-D-myo-inositol, obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate group; major species at pH 7.3.

An anionic phospholipid that is the conjugate base of 2-O-(alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-6-O-(6-acyl-alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol, obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroperoxyicosatrienoic acid that is (9E,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid in which the hydroperoxy substituent is located at position 8R.
A hydroperoxy polyunsaturated fatty acid that is any icosatrienoic fatty acid carrying a single hydroperoxy substituent.
A hydroperoxyicosatrienoic acid that is (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid in which the hydroperoxy substituent is located at position 10.
A hydroperoxyicosatrienoic acid that is (8Z,12E,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid in which the hydroperoxy substituent is located at position 11.
An EpETE that is (5Z,9Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoic acid in which the epoxide function is located across positions 8 and 9.
An octadecanoid that is (9Z,11Z,15Z)-octadecatrienoic acid having an epoxy group located across positions 12 and 13.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of estrone 3-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 16alpha-hydroxyestrone 3-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 16alpha-hydroxyestrone 16-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid conjugate anion formed by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any steroid glucosiduronic acid.
A hydroxyoctadecanoic acid that is octadecanoic acid (stearic acid) which has been substituted by a hydroxy group at position 9.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of testosterone 17-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function; major species at pH 7.3.
An indole alkaloid cation that is the conjugate acid of (3R)-1,2-didehydro-3-hydroxy-16-methoxy-2,3-dihydrotabersonine, obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group. Major species at pH 7.3.
